<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Hivemind:
[B]Yup, Wicked is right.  The troll newbies are rich too, which is not necessarily a good thing btw.  Troll guards are camped a lot and the ground is often littered with stuff that they couldn't be bothered to carry back to Oasis to sell.  I hate to see Troll guard bodies lying around so I generally clean them up, one time I picked up nearly 50pp of gear lying about outside Grobb.

As far as newbies getting rich, a lot of the guard killing powergamers think they are doing them a favour by this.  However I have seen a lot of people who were running around a 4th level in full bronze and minor magic weapons and jewelry become dissatisfied that they can't get good loot off creatures.  Of course this is because they will have to be mid 20s or higher before they can actually fight and kill creatures that have the equivalent of what they were given when they were 4th.

Even assuming there wasn't this gross amount of pp just lying about outside Grobb and Oggok the original posters equipment does not seem far out of line to me.  On an older server low end equipment is pretty cheap and an enterprising, untwinked newbie can do well by going to the places where things they want drop and trying to buy them at discount prices.

Hivemind (aka Grak, Troll Warrior)[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
